      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09A\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table into table `J09A_temp` only for records where the tour starts with `J09A`.\\n\\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09A_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG` using these rules:\\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA` when a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`.\\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` to `EVU`.\\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `500` to `599` to `EVU`.\\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `900` to `999` to `EVU`.\\n   - Set all houses in address area `Wiblingwerde` or `Breckerfeld` to `EVU`.\\n\\n4. Join `J09A_temp` with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the result with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the net customer data table entries.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09A`.\\n   Use exactly these column names in the export:\\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\\n   - `HAUS`\\n   - `ANLAGE`\\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\\n   - `EQUNR`\\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\\n   - `TITLE`\\n   - `FORENAME`\\n   - `SURNAME`\\n   - `STREET`\\n   - `STREETNO`\\n   - `POST_CODE1`\\n   - `CITY1`\\n   - `CITY2`\\n   - `EMAIL`\\n\\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached.\\n   Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\\n\\n11. End the process.\"}",
            "id": "lc_5d6938fa-4258-4783-9143-770e03b4aeb2"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "e2cebc16-7f1a-4354-816a-661d66a6e9b2",
        "tool_call_id": "call_RzLGkg7hNk8JGwjWkvwZB26g",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09A",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table into table `J09A_temp` only for records where the tour starts with `J09A`.\n\n2. Add column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09A_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG` using these rules:\n   - Set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `KSA` when a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`.\n   - Else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to `EVU`.\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1 = 0` to `EVU`.\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `500` to `599` to `EVU`.\n   - Set all houses with `HOUSE_NUM1` from `900` to `999` to `EVU`.\n   - Set all houses in address area `Wiblingwerde` or `Breckerfeld` to `EVU`.\n\n4. Join `J09A_temp` with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the result with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer data from `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER`.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the net customer data table entries.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09A`.\n   Use exactly these column names in the export:\n   - `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`\n   - `HAUS`\n   - `ANLAGE`\n   - `ME_MA_ID`\n   - `EQUNR`\n   - `HOUSE_NUM1`\n   - `ENTSCHEIDUNG`\n   - `TITLE`\n   - `FORENAME`\n   - `SURNAME`\n   - `STREET`\n   - `STREETNO`\n   - `POST_CODE1`\n   - `CITY1`\n   - `CITY2`\n   - `EMAIL`\n\n9. Send an email to `meter.readings@evu.com` with the CSV file attached.\n   Use file path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`.\n\n10. Delete the temporary table.\n\n11. End the process."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
